1
00:00:41,166 --> 00:00:43,084
<i>Did you hear? He got into a fight again.</i>

2
00:00:43,168 --> 00:00:44,335
<i>What? Really?</i>

3
00:00:44,419 --> 00:00:46,087
<i>Talk about annoying.</i>

4
00:00:47,922 --> 00:00:52,051
<i>Again? This is why I was
against taking him in.</i>

5
00:00:52,135 --> 00:00:53,762
<i>Better not get involved with him.</i>

6
00:00:53,845 --> 00:00:55,305
<i>Yeah. Like, look at him.</i>

7
00:00:55,388 --> 00:00:59,059
<i>We had no choice, okay?
Nobody else was willing to take him.</i>

8
00:00:59,142 --> 00:01:01,811
<i>Given that boy's creepy look,
that's a given.</i>

9
00:01:01,895 --> 00:01:05,815
<i>Hey, I told you to dye your hair black!
Why won't you ever listen?</i>

10
00:01:05,899 --> 00:01:07,067
<i>You have no wallet?</i>

11
00:01:07,150 --> 00:01:08,109
<i>That's the guy?</i>

12
00:01:08,193 --> 00:01:09,569
<i>He's the worst.</i>

13
00:01:09,652 --> 00:01:11,863
<i>Besides, what's up with that hair?</i>

14
00:01:11,946 --> 00:01:13,573
<i>Nah, his eyes are worse.</i>

15
00:01:13,656 --> 00:01:15,575
<i>He brings nothing but misfortune.</i>

16
00:01:16,159 --> 00:01:17,952
<i>Disgusting.</i>

17
00:01:42,977 --> 00:01:45,897
TONPU MARKET STREET

18
00:01:46,481 --> 00:01:48,149
Wait for me!

19
00:02:00,954 --> 00:02:02,622
<i>I only like the strong.</i>

20
00:02:03,665 --> 00:02:05,834
<i>I have no interest in the weak.</i>

21
00:02:08,878 --> 00:02:10,964
Listen, I said get out of my way.

22
00:02:11,047 --> 00:02:13,550
Come on, don't be like that.

23
00:02:13,633 --> 00:02:17,554
Don't you wanna hang out?
Isn't there anything you wanna do?

24
00:02:18,346 --> 00:02:20,515
I'd really love...

25
00:02:21,683 --> 00:02:23,935
to smash these eggs into your face.

26
00:02:24,018 --> 00:02:26,855
But my hands are full,
and it'd be a waste,

27
00:02:27,188 --> 00:02:28,857
so I won't!

28
00:02:30,859 --> 00:02:33,319
I like a woman who knows how to bark.

29
00:02:33,403 --> 00:02:36,739
But if you go too far, you might get hurt.

30
00:02:37,490 --> 00:02:38,908
Hey! That hurts!

31
00:02:38,992 --> 00:02:43,163
<i>Weaklings who act all smug,
thinking they're strong...</i>

32
00:02:43,246 --> 00:02:44,789
Let me go!

33
00:02:46,332 --> 00:02:47,333
Huh?

34
00:02:47,417 --> 00:02:50,378
Don't be so lame in the middle of the day.

35
00:02:50,461 --> 00:02:52,755
Huh? What's your problem?

36
00:02:52,839 --> 00:02:54,716
And what's up with that fancy look?

37
00:02:54,799 --> 00:02:56,175
Get lost!

38
00:03:00,763 --> 00:03:02,056
<i>...make me sick!</i>

39
00:03:07,604 --> 00:03:12,942
You've got to have a few screws loose
to even think you're strong.

40
00:03:15,069 --> 00:03:18,781
Be sure you remember my name and my face.

41
00:03:18,865 --> 00:03:21,659
So that the weak avoid me,

42
00:03:21,743 --> 00:03:24,704
and the strong seek me out.

43
00:03:25,288 --> 00:03:26,789
I am...

44
00:03:27,790 --> 00:03:31,836
Haruka Sakura from Furin High School!

45
00:05:12,812 --> 00:05:14,063
Wait!

46
00:05:14,856 --> 00:05:17,400
Hey! I said wait!

47
00:05:18,568 --> 00:05:19,569
Thank you.

48
00:05:26,492 --> 00:05:28,077
Huh? Me?

49
00:05:28,578 --> 00:05:31,289
Who else here would I say that to?

50
00:05:34,876 --> 00:05:37,962
I didn't do it to save you or anything!

51
00:05:38,046 --> 00:05:40,798
I just can't stand those people!

52
00:05:41,466 --> 00:05:44,260
Anyway, are you hungry?

53
00:05:44,343 --> 00:05:46,804
Huh? No, I'm not!

54
00:05:48,514 --> 00:05:52,560
Oh? So you're from out of town?

55
00:05:53,144 --> 00:05:55,605
No wonder I've never seen you.

56
00:05:55,688 --> 00:05:58,816
We don't often see new faces in this town.

57
00:05:58,900 --> 00:06:01,069
Yeah, I'm just another weirdo.

58
00:06:01,152 --> 00:06:05,198
No, that's not what I mean.
It's not about your look.

59
00:06:05,281 --> 00:06:08,618
<i>This town was very unsafe
with a lot of teams and gangs</i>

60
00:06:08,701 --> 00:06:11,913
<i>and whatnot
breaking into fights not too long ago.</i>

61
00:06:11,996 --> 00:06:14,791
<i>So normal people wouldn't
even try to come close.</i>

62
00:06:14,874 --> 00:06:18,544
That said, I also came from out of town.

63
00:06:19,545 --> 00:06:23,049
I'm Kotoha Tachibana. Nice to meet you.

64
00:06:23,132 --> 00:06:27,386
<i>Why is she so friendly?</i>

65
00:06:27,470 --> 00:06:29,263
<i>Most people would be freaked out.</i>

66
00:06:29,347 --> 00:06:32,433
<i>I just pummeled five guys in front of her!</i>

67
00:06:32,517 --> 00:06:34,018
<i>Also...</i>

68
00:06:34,102 --> 00:06:35,937
Hm? You're not gonna eat?

69
00:06:36,020 --> 00:06:38,147
You don't like omelet rice?

70
00:06:38,231 --> 00:06:41,067
I'm eating! I'm gonna dig in now!

71
00:06:42,902 --> 00:06:44,403
<i>It's good!</i>

72
00:06:47,824 --> 00:06:50,076
Can I get a takeoff here?

73
00:06:50,159 --> 00:06:53,162
Huh? You mean takeout?
We don't do that here.

74
00:06:53,246 --> 00:06:55,873
Oh, I see. You don't do that, huh?

75
00:06:55,957 --> 00:06:59,168
Still, you sure have a strange look.

76
00:06:59,252 --> 00:07:01,337
Your hair and eyes split in color.

77
00:07:01,420 --> 00:07:04,048
You don't dye your hair
or wear contact lenses, right?

78
00:07:04,132 --> 00:07:06,425
Huh? You got a problem wi...

79
00:07:06,509 --> 00:07:08,553
Wow, it's like a marble.

80
00:07:08,636 --> 00:07:10,471
I've never seen this color before.

81
00:07:12,306 --> 00:07:14,100
What? You wanna go, huh?

82
00:07:14,183 --> 00:07:16,269
I'm not staring you down for a fight, man.

83
00:07:16,352 --> 00:07:18,604
You're a weird one.

84
00:07:18,688 --> 00:07:22,525
Most people get freaked out,
or try to push me away.

85
00:07:22,608 --> 00:07:25,653
Well, I'm used to seeing crazier people.

86
00:07:25,736 --> 00:07:26,696
Like this.

87
00:07:26,779 --> 00:07:28,030
Like what, exactly?

88
00:07:28,823 --> 00:07:30,116
Is that why?

89
00:07:33,286 --> 00:07:35,455
How you look doesn't matter in a fight.

90
00:07:36,831 --> 00:07:39,208
That's why I came to Furin.

91
00:07:39,292 --> 00:07:40,543
{\an8}FURIN

92
00:07:41,502 --> 00:07:45,131
<i>The school with the lowest average
scores and the strongest brawlers.</i>

93
00:07:45,214 --> 00:07:46,757
<i>The place where failures gather.</i>

94
00:07:46,841 --> 00:07:50,636
<i>Factions are always fighting,
and the underlings unseating their bosses.</i>

95
00:07:50,720 --> 00:07:54,098
<i>Be it Obon or New Year's,
there isn't a day they aren't fighting.</i>

96
00:07:55,141 --> 00:07:57,685
That's where I'll climb to the top!

97
00:07:57,768 --> 00:07:59,896
Oh, that's some pretty big talk.

98
00:07:59,979 --> 00:08:01,314
Not really.

99
00:08:01,397 --> 00:08:04,609
The lowest of the low, hated by all,
worth nothing but their fists,

100
00:08:04,692 --> 00:08:08,112
fighting to become the strongest one
around. Sounds great to me.

101
00:08:08,196 --> 00:08:12,116
It's a battle to determine
the scummiest of the scum.

102
00:08:12,658 --> 00:08:14,744
That suits me perfectly.

103
00:08:15,661 --> 00:08:18,206
You sure have high expectations.

104
00:08:20,791 --> 00:08:24,504
Oh, so that's why you're wearing uniform
even though school starts <i>tomorrow?</i>

105
00:08:24,587 --> 00:08:26,214
You're excited, aren't you?

106
00:08:26,881 --> 00:08:28,424
No, I am not!

107
00:08:28,508 --> 00:08:31,719
This is, um, that! I just moved in
and have no other clothes!

108
00:08:31,802 --> 00:08:35,806
Oh, really? You're pumped for
your new school life, aren't you?

109
00:08:35,890 --> 00:08:37,934
You little... Let's take this outside!

110
00:08:38,017 --> 00:08:40,478
Thanks for the meal, Kotoha-chan.

111
00:08:41,437 --> 00:08:43,981
I left the money on the table.

112
00:08:44,065 --> 00:08:47,693
Okay! Thanks for coming
as always, Yama-jii!

113
00:08:47,777 --> 00:08:49,237
Take care.

114
00:08:49,320 --> 00:08:51,239
Yeah, I'll come again.

115
00:08:51,822 --> 00:08:53,699
Hey, old man.

116
00:08:54,700 --> 00:08:56,452
You forgot your bag.

117
00:08:58,788 --> 00:09:01,207
Oh, goodness.

118
00:09:01,290 --> 00:09:04,669
I've been forgetting things a lot lately.

119
00:09:14,095 --> 00:09:16,097
<i>She's making no sense.</i>

120
00:09:16,806 --> 00:09:18,099
Here.

121
00:09:18,182 --> 00:09:21,978
He said that was a present
for his grandkid.

122
00:09:22,061 --> 00:09:25,273
"You really helped me.
Thank you," he said.

123
00:09:26,107 --> 00:09:27,733
Why are you blushing?

124
00:09:27,817 --> 00:09:30,319
Huh? Shut up!

125
00:09:30,820 --> 00:09:34,240
Besides, this whole town's weird!
Including you!

126
00:09:34,323 --> 00:09:35,157
Huh?

127
00:09:35,241 --> 00:09:37,285
You know how weird I look.

128
00:09:37,368 --> 00:09:41,455
Plus, I'm wearing the uniform of
this area's infamous delinquent school!

129
00:09:41,539 --> 00:09:45,501
How can he... thank someone like me?

130
00:09:45,585 --> 00:09:48,379
Normally people would have
their guard up or suspect me.

131
00:09:48,462 --> 00:09:52,383
Last time I picked up someone's wallet,
they thought I stole it.

132
00:09:52,466 --> 00:09:53,301
POLICEEEE!

133
00:09:53,384 --> 00:09:56,679
He's gotta be more cautious and
check if everything's still inside!

134
00:09:56,762 --> 00:10:00,516
Do you want people to trust you or not?
Make up your mind.

135
00:10:02,602 --> 00:10:06,355
Sakura, it was right for you
to choose Furin.

136
00:10:07,732 --> 00:10:11,861
But you will never be the top of Furin.

137
00:10:12,945 --> 00:10:14,405
No matter what.

138
00:10:14,488 --> 00:10:15,865
Huh?

139
00:10:15,948 --> 00:10:18,784
In your current state,
forget about the top,

140
00:10:18,868 --> 00:10:21,370
no one in Furin would even
give you the time of day.

141
00:10:21,454 --> 00:10:22,830
As if!

142
00:10:22,913 --> 00:10:25,499
You don't even know just how strong I am!

143
00:10:26,042 --> 00:10:28,878
Yeah, you might have some skills,

144
00:10:29,378 --> 00:10:32,632
but that's not enough
to be the top of Furin.

145
00:10:33,215 --> 00:10:34,717
Because...

146
00:10:36,594 --> 00:10:37,928
you are alone.

147
00:10:44,602 --> 00:10:48,481
I'm not so weak that I can't win
without relying on other people!

148
00:10:52,151 --> 00:10:55,196
I'm not talking about
being physically alone.

149
00:10:55,279 --> 00:10:58,908
You should go meet the Furin kids first.

150
00:10:59,700 --> 00:11:03,120
Once you do,
you will understand what I mean.

151
00:11:19,261 --> 00:11:21,430
{\an8}AMAKURA LIQUOR STORE

152
00:11:22,932 --> 00:11:24,225
Yes, hello?

153
00:11:26,185 --> 00:11:28,187
Oh, there you are.

154
00:11:29,563 --> 00:11:32,900
I didn't expect you'd show up on your own.

155
00:11:34,068 --> 00:11:36,362
you Furin punk.

156
00:11:55,297 --> 00:11:57,675
Whoa, there. Ignoring me now?

157
00:11:57,758 --> 00:12:01,470
You're the one who told me not
to forget your name and face,

158
00:12:01,554 --> 00:12:03,597
but you forgot it yourself?

159
00:12:03,681 --> 00:12:06,934
Well, it's not like I can forget
your lame-ass face.

160
00:12:07,017 --> 00:12:10,646
Dyeing your hair and wearing contacts?
Is that supposed to be a cosplay?

161
00:12:10,729 --> 00:12:12,440
Hm? Wait.

162
00:12:12,523 --> 00:12:16,444
That's your real hair?
And you're not wearing any contacts.

163
00:12:16,527 --> 00:12:18,404
Really? That's his real hair?

164
00:12:18,487 --> 00:12:19,822
What is he, a cat?

165
00:12:19,905 --> 00:12:21,824
Meow! Meow!

166
00:12:21,907 --> 00:12:23,617
Disgusting.

167
00:12:25,661 --> 00:12:27,913
<i>This is more like it.</i>

168
00:12:27,997 --> 00:12:30,249
<i>This is the normal reaction.</i>

169
00:12:30,332 --> 00:12:33,627
<i>Everyone is always avoiding
and rejecting me...</i>

170
00:12:33,711 --> 00:12:36,088
<i>I don't care anymore.
I've given up already.</i>

171
00:12:36,172 --> 00:12:37,840
<i>But at the very least...</i>

172
00:12:37,923 --> 00:12:40,676
<i>I want to find some worth in myself...</i>

173
00:12:40,759 --> 00:12:43,804
<i>I thought if I beat the guy
in front of me,</i>

174
00:12:43,888 --> 00:12:46,098
<i>that would make me feel better than him.</i>

175
00:12:46,682 --> 00:12:49,768
<i>But you will never be the top of Furin.</i>

176
00:12:49,852 --> 00:12:52,229
<i>Because you are alone.</i>

177
00:12:55,065 --> 00:12:57,860
You picked the wrong guy to fight.

178
00:12:57,943 --> 00:13:01,197
There ain't a team that'll stay quiet
after their head got hit.

179
00:13:01,822 --> 00:13:04,950
This now a war between us and Furin...

180
00:13:06,327 --> 00:13:08,954
<i>You people were the ones
who didn't want to be near me!</i>

181
00:13:09,830 --> 00:13:14,210
<i>I got a weird and strange look?
I know that better than anyone else!</i>

182
00:13:14,793 --> 00:13:17,796
<i>But what have I ever done
to you guys with that?</i>

183
00:13:19,632 --> 00:13:20,966
<i>This is...</i>

184
00:13:21,050 --> 00:13:22,927
<i>This is who I am!</i>

185
00:13:23,010 --> 00:13:24,929
What the hell are you doing, you punk...

186
00:13:25,012 --> 00:13:27,848
<i>If I'm good at fights...
If I'm the strongest one around...</i>

187
00:13:27,932 --> 00:13:31,936
<i>That means I'm the top, right?
What does it matter if I'm alone?</i>

188
00:13:34,688 --> 00:13:35,606
You...

189
00:14:05,010 --> 00:14:05,928
You little...

190
00:14:18,774 --> 00:14:20,192
What are you doing?

191
00:14:20,276 --> 00:14:22,778
Hey, brat! you better stand still!

192
00:14:22,862 --> 00:14:27,616
You Furin bastards can't do a thing
if we take the townsfolk hostage!

193
00:14:32,913 --> 00:14:33,873
Thanks!

194
00:14:33,956 --> 00:14:35,374
Don't get the wrong idea.

195
00:14:35,457 --> 00:14:37,918
I just hate that guy.

196
00:14:38,460 --> 00:14:40,796
He brought a knife to a fistfight.

197
00:14:41,005 --> 00:14:43,716
You bastards better be
careful about how you fight.

198
00:14:50,472 --> 00:14:52,558
I can read you like a book.

199
00:15:04,653 --> 00:15:06,196
<i>Dammit!</i>

200
00:15:06,280 --> 00:15:09,199
<i>This ain't ever gonna end
if I gotta keep protecting her.</i>

201
00:15:09,283 --> 00:15:12,202
<i>Besides, why on earth
am I even protecting her?</i>

202
00:15:12,286 --> 00:15:16,999
<i>Nothing good ever comes from
doing something for other people!</i>

203
00:15:27,092 --> 00:15:29,595
Ouch!

204
00:15:31,013 --> 00:15:32,306
<i>See?</i>

205
00:15:32,431 --> 00:15:35,684
<i>This is why I shouldn't be
worrying about other people.</i>

206
00:15:36,644 --> 00:15:37,895
Sakura!

207
00:15:39,229 --> 00:15:42,566
<i>Just what the heck... am I even doing?</i>

208
00:15:43,525 --> 00:15:44,902
<i>What am I trying to do?</i>

209
00:15:47,196 --> 00:15:50,157
Are you a first-year?
Thanks for being here.

210
00:15:51,659 --> 00:15:54,328
<i>A Furin uniform?</i>

211
00:15:58,290 --> 00:15:59,875
Kotoha-chan.

212
00:16:01,085 --> 00:16:05,381
Don't tell him that you
were caught up in trouble, okay?

213
00:16:12,972 --> 00:16:14,390
Hey, you bastards.

214
00:16:21,105 --> 00:16:25,109
To swing this kind of thing in this town
is a serious matter...

215
00:16:27,861 --> 00:16:29,905
and you better know what it means!

216
00:16:31,573 --> 00:16:35,577
Oh, come on! There are way
fewer people than what she said!

217
00:16:35,661 --> 00:16:38,247
We could've handled this with two people.

218
00:16:38,831 --> 00:16:39,999
<i>Why...</i>

219
00:16:40,582 --> 00:16:43,335
<i>are Furin students helping me?</i>

220
00:16:43,419 --> 00:16:44,420
It's Furin!

221
00:16:44,503 --> 00:16:45,963
It's Furin's Hiragi!

222
00:16:46,046 --> 00:16:49,216
Don't be chicken!
There are only four more people!

223
00:16:49,299 --> 00:16:50,551
Go!

224
00:16:51,802 --> 00:16:55,097
Matsumoto, Kaji, Yanagida!

225
00:16:55,180 --> 00:16:57,891
If you let a single one
of them get past us,

226
00:16:57,975 --> 00:16:59,351
I'll kick your ass!

227
00:17:01,353 --> 00:17:02,521
There you go!

228
00:17:12,114 --> 00:17:13,365
Come on! Bring it!

229
00:17:17,828 --> 00:17:19,079
<i>Crap!</i>

230
00:17:21,582 --> 00:17:23,459
If you're hurt, then stand back!

231
00:17:24,752 --> 00:17:27,421
Don't order me around! That guy was mine!

232
00:17:27,504 --> 00:17:29,339
Just stay still, you moron!

233
00:17:29,423 --> 00:17:31,383
If you keep wobbling around...

234
00:17:31,467 --> 00:17:33,218
we won't be able to protect you!

235
00:17:46,482 --> 00:17:48,525
Go! Get them!

236
00:17:50,444 --> 00:17:53,197
What? What's going on?

237
00:17:54,448 --> 00:17:58,368
I told you that this town was
very unsafe with a lot of teams,

238
00:17:58,452 --> 00:18:02,498
gangs and whatnot breaking
into fights not too long ago, didn't I?

239
00:18:03,082 --> 00:18:05,084
To be precise, it was until two years ago.

240
00:18:05,167 --> 00:18:07,628
Since then, the town has changed.

241
00:18:07,711 --> 00:18:11,590
<i>The people who changed it
were the students of Furin High.</i>

242
00:18:12,132 --> 00:18:15,803
The first thing they did was
set up a sign in front of town.

243
00:18:17,471 --> 00:18:21,391
If you don't know how to use a bat,
at least learn how to read!

244
00:18:22,392 --> 00:18:25,646
"Anyone past this point,
who causes pain...

245
00:18:25,729 --> 00:18:27,856
who brings destruction,

246
00:18:27,940 --> 00:18:29,608
who holds evil in their heart..."

247
00:18:29,691 --> 00:18:34,738
They originally had Furin High's
name written next to it...

248
00:18:34,822 --> 00:18:38,909
Eventually,
the townsfolk gave them a new name.

249
00:18:39,576 --> 00:18:43,372
To the students who fight
to protect the town...

250
00:18:43,705 --> 00:18:48,502
"...will be purged by Bofurin
without exception!"

251
00:18:49,211 --> 00:18:50,838
{\an8}<i>Bofurin.</i>

252
00:18:50,921 --> 00:18:52,548
{\an8}<i>The shield of this town.</i>

253
00:18:53,757 --> 00:18:55,676
<i>The Wind Breaker.</i>

254
00:18:59,429 --> 00:19:01,473
-Thank you, guys!
-Thanks a lot!

255
00:19:01,557 --> 00:19:03,892
You boys are life savers!
Thank you always.

256
00:19:05,144 --> 00:19:07,855
The lowest of the low, hated by all.

257
00:19:07,938 --> 00:19:10,732
That was the case two years ago.

258
00:19:10,816 --> 00:19:13,819
They're still fighting, yes.

259
00:19:14,444 --> 00:19:17,739
-Granny! Didn't you say 100 people?
-But they're now loved and

260
00:19:17,823 --> 00:19:21,201
-needed by everyone in town.
-My eyesight has gotten so bad lately.

261
00:19:21,743 --> 00:19:23,579
<i>What the heck is that?</i>

262
00:19:24,121 --> 00:19:27,749
<i>That sounds like a hero of justice.</i>

263
00:19:29,877 --> 00:19:33,297
-You were cool when you bent that bat!
<i>-They're delinquents and fight...</i>

264
00:19:33,380 --> 00:19:37,384
-Anyone could pull that off.
<i>-...but no one is afraid or avoiding them...</i>

265
00:19:37,467 --> 00:19:39,386
<i>They've been accepted here.</i>

266
00:19:39,469 --> 00:19:40,637
<i>Huh?</i>

267
00:19:42,723 --> 00:19:45,225
You were amazing too out there!

268
00:19:45,309 --> 00:19:47,978
You did well fending them off
on your own at first!

269
00:19:48,061 --> 00:19:51,064
Boy, they hurt your leg, didn't they?

270
00:19:51,148 --> 00:19:53,483
We need to treat it right away.

271
00:19:57,571 --> 00:19:59,323
Stop it!

272
00:20:07,289 --> 00:20:08,707
Sakura.

273
00:20:09,958 --> 00:20:13,128
I said you were alone.

274
00:20:13,212 --> 00:20:14,296
But...

275
00:20:14,922 --> 00:20:19,468
I could tell that you didn't become one
because you wanted to.

276
00:20:20,886 --> 00:20:24,181
But the people of this town need you.

277
00:20:24,264 --> 00:20:25,307
TONPU MARKET STREET

278
00:20:25,807 --> 00:20:27,476
Don't act like you know anything!

279
00:20:27,559 --> 00:20:30,520
I don't need anyone and
I won't associate myself with anyone...

280
00:20:30,604 --> 00:20:31,855
Then why...

281
00:20:32,481 --> 00:20:35,359
<i>did you give Yama-jii
the present he forgot?</i>

282
00:20:36,026 --> 00:20:39,071
Why did you save me?

283
00:20:40,447 --> 00:20:42,699
You haven't given up on other people.

284
00:20:43,200 --> 00:20:44,660
You don't have to.

285
00:20:45,452 --> 00:20:49,206
At the very least, I'm facing you head-on.

286
00:20:50,207 --> 00:20:53,210
So you should lift
your face up to us, too.

287
00:20:54,586 --> 00:20:56,463
Once you do, I'm sure...

288
00:21:01,343 --> 00:21:04,012
you will become the person you want to be.

289
00:21:15,899 --> 00:21:18,318
Delinquents trying to play the hero?

290
00:21:18,402 --> 00:21:21,947
If all you gotta do is win in a fight,
then even I can do that!

291
00:21:22,030 --> 00:21:25,826
What is all this Bofurin crap?
What is this "shield of the town" crap?

292
00:21:25,909 --> 00:21:30,330
That's so damn cool!

293
00:21:37,254 --> 00:21:40,966
<i>Can I be with someone in this place?</i>

294
00:21:49,057 --> 00:21:52,185
<i>This is the story of a boy
who's good for nothing but his fist,</i>

295
00:21:52,269 --> 00:21:54,730
<i>the lowest of the low, and hated by all,</i>

296
00:21:54,813 --> 00:21:57,524
<i>became the hero of the town.</i>

297
00:23:31,493 --> 00:23:35,956
{\an8}I came to this town,
to Furin High, to fight.

298
00:23:36,540 --> 00:23:39,334
{\an8}However, that school,
now known as Bofurin,

299
00:23:39,417 --> 00:23:41,795
{\an8}turned out to be a school
that protects the town.

300
00:23:42,420 --> 00:23:47,634
"Anyone who causes pain,
who brings destruction,

301
00:23:47,717 --> 00:23:54,182
who holds evil in their heart, will be
purged by Bofurin without exception," huh.

302
00:23:55,517 --> 00:23:58,895
{\an8}Furin High looks like
it'll be quite a fun place.

